ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a faculty research seminar that allows junior and senior faculty at other research universities to present early and late stage work to receive feedback from colleagues. I would in general recommend this course to students as a way to gain exposure to new research in our field and meet interesting junior and senior faculty at other departments.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Honestly, this semester I am not sure how the seminars deepened my knowledge of the discipline. The speakers and papers were below the quality that I expected for a university of Yale's caliber. The topics covered were also far from my own research interests, so maybe this is in part why I found the seminar not particularly inspiring.
